==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bifid
<hw>Bi"fid</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>bifidus</ets>; <ets>bis</ets> twice + root of <ets>findere</ets> to
cleave or split: cf. F. <ets>bifide</ets>.]</ety> <def>Cleft to the
middle or slightly beyond the middle; opening with a cleft; divided by a
linear sinus, with straight margins.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bifidate</ent>⟦br⟧
